core.tut.pori.dao.clause

Class OrSubClause

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.tut.pori.dao.clause.WhereClause
      • core.tut.pori.dao.clause.AndSubClause
        • core.tut.pori.dao.clause.OrSubClause
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SQLClause

    public class OrSubClause
extends AndSubClause
    Create and SQL sub-clause with OR prefix. WHERE OR (CLAUSE [OR] CLAUSE [OR] ...), the inner operation ([OR]) depends on the type of the clause provided as a sub-clause. This class is provided for convenience. In some cases the same functionality could be achieved by a combination of multiple OR clauses without sub-clause. Note: not adding any clauses will make this clause a no-op.
